            <description path="C:/Qt/5.11.1/Src/qt3d/examples/qt3d/simplecustommaterial/doc/src/simplecustommaterial.qdoc" line="28" column="4">
                <brief>Demonstrates creating a custom material in Qt 3D.</brief>
                <image href="images/simple-custom-material.jpg"/>
                <para>
                    <italic>This</italic> example demonstrates creating a simple custom material.</para>
                <section id="running-the-example">
                    <heading level="1">Running the Example</heading>
                    <para>To run the example from <link raw="Qt Creator Manual" href="http://doc.qt.io/qtcreator/index.html" type="page" page="Qt Creator Manual">Qt Creator</link>, open the <bold>Welcome</bold> mode and select the example from <bold>Examples</bold>. For more information, visit <link raw="Qt Creator: Building and Running an Example" href="http://doc.qt.io/qtcreator/creator-build-example-application.html" type="page" page="Qt Creator: Building and Running an Example">Building and Running an Example</link>.</para>
                </section>
                <section id="specifying-the-scene">
                    <heading level="1">Specifying the Scene</heading>
                    <para>The example uses <link raw="Scene3D" href="qml-qt3d-scene3d-scene3d.html" type="">Scene3D</link> to render a scene which will use the custom material. The scene contains a plane model, which uses the custom material.</para>
                    <quotefromfile>simplecustommaterial/PlaneModel.qml</quotefromfile>
                    <skipto>Entity</skipto>
                    <printto></printto>
                </section>
                <section id="specifying-the-material">
                    <heading level="1">Specifying the Material</heading>
                    <para>The material is specified in <link raw="simplecustommaterial/SimpleMaterial.qml" href="qt3d-simplecustommaterial-simplematerial-qml.html" type="page" page="simplecustommaterial::simplecustommaterial/SimpleMaterial.qml">SimpleMaterial.qml</link> using <link raw="Material" href="qml-qt3d-render-material.html" type="">Material</link> type. First the material specifies parameters, which are mapped to the corresponding uniforms in the shaders so that they can be changed from the qml.</para>
                    <snippet location="simplecustommaterial/SimpleMaterial.qml" path="C:/Qt/5.11.1/Src/qt3d/examples/qt3d/simplecustommaterial/SimpleMaterial.qml" identifier="0"/>
                    <para>Next we specify which shaders are loaded. Separate versions of the shaders are provided for OpenGL ES 2 and OpenGL renderers.</para>
                    <snippet location="simplecustommaterial/SimpleMaterial.qml" path="C:/Qt/5.11.1/Src/qt3d/examples/qt3d/simplecustommaterial/SimpleMaterial.qml" identifier="1"/>
                    <para>In the vertex shader we simply transform the position by the transformation matrices.</para>
                    <quotefromfile>simplecustommaterial/shaders/gl3/simpleColor.vert</quotefromfile>
                    <skipto>void main()</skipto>
                    <printto></printto>
                    <para>In the fragment shader we simply set the fragment color to be the maincolor specified in the material.</para>
                    <quotefromfile>simplecustommaterial/shaders/gl3/simpleColor.frag</quotefromfile>
                    <skipto>uniform vec3 maincolor;</skipto>
                    <printuntil>;</printuntil>
                    <skipto>void main()</skipto>
                    <printto></printto>
                    <para>Next, we create <link raw="ShaderProgram" href="qml-qt3d-render-shaderprogram.html" type="">ShaderPrograms</link> from the shaders.</para>
                    <snippet location="simplecustommaterial/SimpleMaterial.qml" path="C:/Qt/5.11.1/Src/qt3d/examples/qt3d/simplecustommaterial/SimpleMaterial.qml" identifier="2"/>
                    <para>Finally the shader programs are used in the Techniques corresponding to a specific Api profile.</para>
                    <snippet location="simplecustommaterial/SimpleMaterial.qml" path="C:/Qt/5.11.1/Src/qt3d/examples/qt3d/simplecustommaterial/SimpleMaterial.qml" identifier="3"/>
                </section>
            </description>
